        <headline>Beach Hazards Statement issued August 19 at 7:27AM EDT until August 20 at 2:00AM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...High wave action, strong currents, and dangerous
swimming conditions expected. Piers may be heavily swamped by
waves.

* WHERE...Ottawa, Allegan and Van Buren counties.

* WHEN...From 5 PM EDT this afternoon through late tonight.

* IMPACTS...Strong currents can pull swimmers into deeper water
and high waves can sweep people off piers.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds and waves will build this afternoon
and continue through this evening. North facing beaches and
north sides of piers will be especially dangerous. Especially
Holland State Park, and North Beach at South Haven will see
waves of 2 to 5 feet.
</description>
        <instruction>Remain out of the water to avoid hazardous swimming conditions
and do not venture out on piers. Please check with your local
authorities on potential beach closures.</instruction>
